00:57:56,423 --> 00:57:58,292
I pulled something from Dad's archives.

807
00:58:00,051 --> 00:58:01,328
Felt timely.

808
00:58:05,578 --> 00:58:08,690
FDR signed the Lend-Lease bill
with these in 1941.

809
00:58:09,686 --> 00:58:12,343
Provided support to the Allies
when they needed it most.

810
00:58:12,772 --> 00:58:14,812
Some would say it brought
our country closer to war.

811
00:58:16,484 --> 00:58:18,504
See? If not for these,
you would not be here.

812
00:58:20,639 --> 00:58:21,640
I'm trying to...

813
00:58:22,056 --> 00:58:23,157
what do you call it?

814
00:58:23,325 --> 00:58:24,976
That's an olive branch.

815
00:58:26,119 --> 00:58:27,221
Is that what you call it?

816
00:58:29,039 --> 00:58:31,099
Is Pepper here? I didn't see her.

817
00:58:32,751 --> 00:58:33,715
We're...

818
00:58:34,574 --> 00:58:35,445
kinda...

819
00:58:35,726 --> 00:58:37,495
Well, not kinda,
Pregnant?

820
00:58:37,756 --> 00:58:39,257
No. Definitely not.

821
00:58:39,424 --> 00:58:40,618
We're taking a break.

822
00:58:41,508 --> 00:58:42,626
It's nobody's fault.

823
00:58:44,327 --> 00:58:46,126
I'm so sorry, Tony. I didn't know.

824
00:58:46,617 --> 00:58:49,727
A few years ago, I almost lost her,
so I trashed all my suits.

825
00:58:50,518 --> 00:58:52,174
Then, we had to mop up HYDRA,

826
00:58:52,187 --> 00:58:54,147
and then Ultron. My fault.

827
00:58:55,065 --> 00:58:57,876
And then, and then, and then,
I never stopped.

828
00:58:58,443 --> 00:59:00,520
Because the truth is
I don't wanna stop.

829
00:59:02,197 --> 00:59:03,627
I don't wanna lose her.

830
00:59:04,407 --> 00:59:06,790
I thought maybe the Accords
could split the difference.

831
00:59:10,664 --> 00:59:12,326
In her defense, I'm a handful.

832
00:59:14,042 --> 00:59:15,948
Yet, Dad was a pain in the ass,

833
00:59:16,586 --> 00:59:18,208
but he and Mom always made it work.

834
00:59:18,389 --> 00:59:19,934
I'm glad Howard got married.

835
00:59:20,715 --> 00:59:22,514
I only knew him
when he was young and single.

836
00:59:22,662 --> 00:59:24,398
Oh, really?
You two knew each other?

837
00:59:24,914 --> 00:59:26,028
He never mentioned that.

838
00:59:26,309 --> 00:59:28,366
Maybe only a thousand times.

839
00:59:29,641 --> 00:59:31,017
God, I hated you.

840
00:59:33,019 --> 00:59:34,505
I don't mean to make things difficult.

841
00:59:34,602 --> 00:59:36,534
I know, because
you're a very polite person.

842
00:59:37,732 --> 00:59:40,026
If I see a situation pointed south,

843
00:59:40,860 --> 00:59:42,061
I can't ignore it.

844
00:59:42,601 --> 00:59:43,822
Sometimes I wish I could.

845
00:59:43,989 --> 00:59:45,031
No, you don't.

846
00:59:48,119 --> 00:59:49,132
No, I don't.

847
00:59:50,750 --> 00:59:51,536
Sometimes...

848
00:59:51,538 --> 00:59:54,112
Sometimes I wanna
punch you in your perfect teeth.

849
00:59:55,166 --> 00:59:56,626
But I don't wanna see you gone.

850
00:59:57,377 --> 00:59:58,613
We need you, Cap.

851
00:59:59,587 --> 01:00:02,534
So far, nothing's happened
that can't be undone, if you sign.

852
01:00:03,466 --> 01:00:05,343
We can make the last 24 hours legit.

853
01:00:05,510 --> 01:00:07,608
Barnes gets transferred
to an American psych-center,

854
01:00:07,610 --> 01:00:09,438
instead of a Wakandan prison.

855
01:00:21,879 --> 01:00:23,521
I'm not saying it's impossible but...

856
01:00:23,882 --> 01:00:25,333
there would have to be safeguards.

857
01:00:25,335 --> 01:00:26,059
Sure.

858
01:00:26,656 --> 01:00:28,191
Once we put out the PR fire,

859
01:00:28,251 --> 01:00:30,152
those documents can be amended.

860
01:00:30,715 --> 01:00:32,832
I'd file a motion to have
you and Wanda reinstated.

861
01:00:32,834 --> 01:00:34,008
Wanda? What about Wanda?

862
01:00:34,126 --> 01:00:36,361
She's fine. She's confined
to the compound, currently.

863
01:00:36,363 --> 01:00:37,607
Vision's keeping her company.

864
01:00:37,609 --> 01:00:38,811
Oh, God, Tony.

865
01:00:38,813 --> 01:00:40,251
Every time. every time I think

866
01:00:40,253 --> 01:00:42,724
you see things the right way,
It's 100 acres with a lap pool.

867
01:00:42,726 --> 01:00:45,117
It's got a screening room.
There's worse ways to protect people.

868
01:00:45,121 --> 01:00:46,164
Protection?

869
01:00:46,593 --> 01:00:47,677
Is that how you see this?

870
01:00:47,691 --> 01:00:49,904
This is protection?
It's internment, Tony.

871
01:00:49,906 --> 01:00:51,382
She's not a US citizen.
Oh, come on, Tony.

872
01:00:51,389 --> 01:00:53,327
And they don't grant visas
to weapons of mass destruction.

873
01:00:53,329 --> 01:00:55,075
She's a kid!
Give me a break!

874
01:00:56,325 --> 01:00:57,888
I'm doing what has to be done.

875
01:00:59,035 --> 01:01:00,640
To stave off something worse.

876
01:01:03,693 --> 01:01:05,170
You keep telling yourself that.

877
01:01:08,940 --> 01:01:10,509
Hate to break up the set.

878
01:01:17,457 --> 01:01:18,834
<i>Hello, Mr Barnes.</i>

879
01:01:19,415 --> 01:01:21,946
<i>I've been sent by
the United Nations to evaluate you.</i>

880
01:01:22,428 --> 01:01:23,639
<i>Do you mind if I sit?</i>

881
01:01:29,677 --> 01:01:31,388
<i>Your first name is James?</i>

882
01:01:32,662 --> 01:01:34,281
The receipt for your gear.

883
01:01:36,643 --> 01:01:38,311
Bird costume? Come on.

884
01:01:38,368 --> 01:01:39,478
I didn't write it.

885
01:01:46,272 --> 01:01:47,740
<i>I'm not here to judge you.</i>

886
01:01:48,339 --> 01:01:50,348
<i>I just want to ask you a few questions.</i>

887
01:01:51,491 --> 01:01:53,343
<i>Do you know where you are, James?</i>

888
01:01:56,913 --> 01:01:59,624
<i>I can't help you if you
don't talk to me, James.</i>

889
01:02:00,583 --> 01:02:02,023
<i>My name is BUCKY.</i>

890
01:02:11,177 --> 01:02:12,187
Hello?

891
01:02:19,769 --> 01:02:20,563
Hey!

892
01:02:21,071 --> 01:02:22,550
A delivery for you.

893
01:02:27,597 --> 01:02:28,149
Ok

894
01:02:29,624 --> 01:02:31,890
Yeah. Sign here please.

895
01:02:32,828 --> 01:02:33,857
Here?
Yes.

896
01:02:41,486 --> 01:02:43,825
Why would the Task Force
release this photo to begin with?

897
01:02:44,419 --> 01:02:46,713
Get the word out,
involve as many eyes as we can?

898
01:02:46,762 --> 01:02:47,481
Right.

899
01:02:48,110 --> 01:02:49,698
It's a good way to flush
a guy out of hiding.

900
01:02:49,924 --> 01:02:51,730
Set off a bomb, get your picture taken.

901
01:02:51,999 --> 01:02:54,063
Get seven billion people looking
for the Winter Soldier.

902
01:02:54,155 --> 01:02:55,990
You're saying someone
framed him to find him?

903
01:02:56,069 --> 01:02:58,339
Steve, we looked for the guy for
two years and found nothing.

904
01:02:58,558 --> 01:03:00,606
We didn't bomb the UN.
That turns a lot of heads.

905
01:03:00,643 --> 01:03:02,037
Yeah, but that doesn't guarantee that

906
01:03:02,039 --> 01:03:03,267
whoever framed him would get him.

907
01:03:03,269 --> 01:03:04,804
It guarantees that we would.

908
01:03:11,346 --> 01:03:12,346
Yeah.

909
01:03:15,061 --> 01:03:16,279
Tell me BUCKY.

910
01:03:16,743 --> 01:03:18,752
You've seen a great deal, haven't you?

911
01:03:20,658 --> 01:03:22,457
<i>I don't wanna talk about it.</i>

912
01:03:23,249 --> 01:03:25,650
You fear that if you open your mouth,

913
01:03:25,814 --> 01:03:27,554
the horrors might never stop.

914
01:03:31,533 --> 01:03:32,618
Don't worry.

915
01:03:35,637 --> 01:03:37,831
We only have to talk about one.

916
01:03:49,001 --> 01:03:50,100
Hey! What is this?

917
01:03:50,593 --> 01:03:51,426
What this?

918
01:04:01,867 --> 01:04:03,723
Come on, guys,
get me eyes on Barnes.

919
01:04:04,958 --> 01:04:07,544
Friday, get me a source on that outage.

920
01:04:08,836 --> 01:04:10,680
Sub-level five, East Wing.

921
01:04:14,446 --> 01:04:15,905
What the hell is this?

922
01:04:15,939 --> 01:04:17,566
Why don't we discuss your home?

923
01:04:17,804 --> 01:04:18,804
Not Romania.

924
01:04:19,120 --> 01:04:20,772
Certainly not Brooklyn no.

925
01:04:22,188 --> 01:04:22,884
I mean...

926
01:04:24,041 --> 01:04:25,576
your real home.

927
01:04:31,397 --> 01:04:32,472
Longing

928
01:04:33,486 --> 01:04:34,203
No.

929
01:04:35,947 --> 01:04:36,656
Rusted.

930
01:04:37,193 --> 01:04:37,943
Stop.

931
01:04:38,372 --> 01:04:39,614
Seventeen.

932
01:04:41,828 --> 01:04:42,544
Stop.

933
01:04:44,780 --> 01:04:46,206
Daybreak.

934
01:04:52,463 --> 01:04:53,412
Furnace.

935
01:04:56,009 --> 01:04:57,009
Nine.

936
01:05:00,054 --> 01:05:01,049
Benign.

937
01:05:04,684 --> 01:05:06,235
Homecoming.

938
01:05:07,061 --> 01:05:07,881
One.

939
01:05:09,522 --> 01:05:10,522
Freight car.

940
01:05:26,924 --> 01:05:28,050
Soldier?

941
01:05:31,062 --> 01:05:32,420
Ready to comply.

942
01:05:33,254 --> 01:05:34,673
Mission report.

943
01:05:35,479 --> 01:05:37,053
December 16,

944
01:05:37,055 --> 01:05:38,675
1991.

945
01:05:49,312 --> 01:05:50,308
Help me.

946
01:05:51,272 --> 01:05:52,177
Help.

947
01:05:55,276 --> 01:05:56,277
Get up.

948
01:05:59,739 --> 01:06:01,256
Who are you? What do you want?

949
01:06:02,950 --> 01:06:04,952
To see an empire fall.

950
01:06:36,726 --> 01:06:37,380
Hey.

951
01:06:44,826 --> 01:06:46,367
Evac all civilians.

952
01:06:46,369 --> 01:06:48,880
Get me a perimeter around the building,
and gunships in the air.

953
01:06:48,882 --> 01:06:50,383
Please tell me you brought a suit.

954
01:06:50,456 --> 01:06:53,040
Sure did. It's a lovely Tom Ford,
three-piece, two-button.

955
01:06:53,042 --> 01:06:54,544
I'm an active-duty non-combatant.

956
01:06:55,169 --> 01:06:56,090
Follow me.

957
01:07:13,354 --> 01:07:14,700
<i>We're in position.</i>

958
01:07:46,929 --> 01:07:48,948
You could at least recognise me.

959
01:08:41,984 --> 01:08:43,194
Damn it.

960
01:10:20,499 --> 01:10:22,710
<i>He asked me again
if you were going to be there.</i>

961
01:10:22,793 --> 01:10:24,754
<i>I said I wasn't sure.</i>

962
01:10:24,837 --> 01:10:27,406
<i>You should have seen his
little face. Just try, ok?</i>

963
01:10:28,341 --> 01:10:29,698
<i>I'm going to bed.</i>

964
01:10:30,259 --> 01:10:31,577
<i>I love you.</i>

965
01:10:35,556 --> 01:10:39,560
<i>James Barnes the suspect
in the UN Vienna bombing,</i>

966
01:10:39,562 --> 01:10:40,860
<i>escaped custody today.</i>

967
01:10:41,296 --> 01:10:44,398
<i>Also missing Avenger
Captain Steve Rogers,</i>

968
01:10:44,400 --> 01:10:45,400
<i>and Sam Wilson.</i>

969
01:11:09,548 --> 01:11:10,549
Hey, Cap!

970
01:11:23,354 --> 01:11:24,438
Steve.

971
01:11:25,439 --> 01:11:26,906
Which BUCKY am I talking to?

972
01:11:29,276 --> 01:11:31,135
Your mom's name was Sarah.

973
01:11:35,491 --> 01:11:38,403
You used to wear newspapers
in your shoes.

974
01:11:40,327 --> 01:11:41,537
Can't read that in a museum.

975
01:11:41,539 --> 01:11:43,364
Just like that,
we're supposed to be cool?

976
01:11:43,747 --> 01:11:44,944
What did I do?

977
01:11:45,167 --> 01:11:45,918
Enough.

978
01:11:45,936 --> 01:11:47,729
Oh, God, I knew this would happen.

979
01:11:47,974 --> 01:11:50,268
Everything HYDRA
put inside me is still there.

980
01:11:50,799 --> 01:11:52,735
All he had to do
was say the goddamn words.

981
01:11:52,737 --> 01:11:54,267
Who was he?
I don't know.

982
01:11:54,427 --> 01:11:55,469
People are dead.

983
01:11:55,650 --> 01:11:56,841
The bombing, the setup,

984
01:11:56,843 --> 01:11:58,971
the doctor did all that just
to get 10 minutes with you.

985
01:11:59,057 --> 01:12:00,933
I need you to do better
than I don't know.

986
01:12:04,645 --> 01:12:06,734
He wanted to know about Siberia.

987
01:12:09,942 --> 01:12:11,403
Where I was kept.

988
01:12:13,695 --> 01:12:15,446
He wanted to know exactly where.

989
01:12:15,448 --> 01:12:16,721
Why would he need to know that?

990
01:12:19,744 --> 01:12:22,079
Because I'm not
the only Winter Soldier.

991
01:13:15,800 --> 01:13:17,138
It hurts!

992
01:13:54,547 --> 01:13:55,715
Good work.

993
01:14:07,393 --> 01:14:08,769
Get me out of here.

994
01:14:22,783 --> 01:14:23,909
Who were they?

995
01:14:24,076 --> 01:14:25,661
Their most elite death squad.

996
01:14:25,828 --> 01:14:28,279
More kills than anyone
in HYDRA history.

997
01:14:28,528 --> 01:14:29,796
And that was before the serum.

998
01:14:29,804 --> 01:14:31,066
They all turn out like you?

999
01:14:31,247 --> 01:14:32,059
Worse.

1000
01:14:32,785 --> 01:14:33,593
The doctor,

1001
01:14:33,799 --> 01:14:34,734
could he control them?

1002
01:14:35,405 --> 01:14:36,319
Enough.

1003
01:14:37,155 --> 01:14:38,718
He said he wanted
to see an empire fall.

1004
01:14:38,742 --> 01:14:40,036
With these guys, he could do it.

1005
01:14:40,184 --> 01:14:43,220
They speak 30 languages,
can hide in plain sight,

1006
01:14:43,404 --> 01:14:45,614
infiltrate, assassinate, destabilize.

1007
01:14:45,620 --> 01:14:47,966
They can take a whole
country down in one night,

1008
01:14:47,977 --> 01:14:49,320
you'd never see them coming.

1009
01:14:51,512 --> 01:14:53,656
This would have been
a lot easier a week ago.

1010
01:14:54,239 --> 01:14:56,231
If we call Tony.
No, he won't believe us.

1011
01:14:56,311 --> 01:14:57,247
Even if he did.

1012
01:14:57,249 --> 01:14:59,158
Who knows if the Accords
would let him help.

1013
01:15:00,743 --> 01:15:01,744
We're on our own.

1014
01:15:02,990 --> 01:15:03,990
Maybe not.

1015
01:15:05,910 --> 01:15:06,936
I know a guy.

1016
01:15:08,123 --> 01:15:11,505
I don't suppose you have
any idea where they are?

1017
01:15:11,623 --> 01:15:12,623
We will.

1018
01:15:12,625 --> 01:15:14,210
GSG 9's got the borders covered.

1019
01:15:14,212 --> 01:15:16,005
Recon's flying 24/7.

1020
01:15:16,501 --> 01:15:17,810
They'll get a hit. We'll handle it.

1021
01:15:17,812 --> 01:15:19,689
You don't get it, Stark.
It's not yours to handle.

1022
01:15:19,959 --> 01:15:22,121
It's clear you can't be objective.

1023
01:15:22,394 --> 01:15:23,896
I'm putting Special Ops on this.

1024
01:15:23,956 --> 01:15:25,342
What happens
when the shooting starts?

1025
01:15:25,344 --> 01:15:26,637
What, do you kill Steve Rogers?

1026
01:15:26,639 --> 01:15:27,961
If we're provoked.

1027
01:15:28,140 --> 01:15:31,435
Barnes would have been eliminated
in Romania if it wasn't for Rogers.

1028
01:15:31,765 --> 01:15:35,251
There are dead people
who would be alive now.

1029
01:15:36,482 --> 01:15:38,070
Feel free to check my math.

1030
01:15:38,072 --> 01:15:41,035
All due respect you're not gonna solve
this with boys and bullets, Ross.

1031
01:15:41,387 --> 01:15:42,527
You got to let us bring them in.

1032
01:15:42,529 --> 01:15:44,489
How would that end
any differently than last time?

1033
01:15:44,650 --> 01:15:47,666
Because this time I won't be
wearing loafers and a silk shirt.

1034
01:15:48,604 --> 01:15:50,604
72 hours, guaranteed.

1035
01:15:51,019 --> 01:15:52,118
36 hours.

1036
01:15:54,359 --> 01:15:55,455
Barnes.

1037
01:15:57,114 --> 01:15:58,282
Rogers.

1038
01:15:59,038 --> 01:16:00,038
Wilson.

1039
01:16:00,214 --> 01:16:01,124
Thank you, sir.

1040
01:16:05,956 --> 01:16:07,857
My left arm is numb. Is that normal?

1041
01:16:10,975 --> 01:16:12,059
You alright?

1042
01:16:12,826 --> 01:16:13,669
Always.

1043
01:16:17,398 --> 01:16:19,328
36 hours. Jeez.

1044
01:16:19,817 --> 01:16:21,777
We're seriously understaffed.

1045
01:16:22,027 --> 01:16:22,920
Oh, yeah.

1046
01:16:23,362 --> 01:16:25,411
It'd be great if we had
a Hulk right about now.

1047
01:16:25,474 --> 01:16:26,413
Any shot?

1048
01:16:28,436 --> 01:16:30,756
You really think he'd be on our side?

1049
01:16:31,109 --> 01:16:31,919
No.

1050
01:16:32,288 --> 01:16:33,364
I have an idea.

1051
01:16:33,747 --> 01:16:34,580
Me, too.

1052
01:16:35,251 --> 01:16:36,072
Where's yours?

1053
01:16:36,250 --> 01:16:37,432
Downstairs.

1054
01:16:38,210 --> 01:16:39,378
Where's yours?

1055
01:17:01,517 --> 01:17:02,204
Hey, May.

1056
01:17:02,901 --> 01:17:03,577
Hey.

1057
01:17:06,452 --> 01:17:07,827
How was school today?

1058
01:17:08,115 --> 01:17:09,026
It was ok.

1059
01:17:09,447 --> 01:17:11,540
This crazy car parked outside.

1060
01:17:15,331 --> 01:17:16,346
Oh, Mr Parker.

1061
01:17:19,293 --> 01:17:21,135
What... What are you doing...

1062
01:17:21,503 --> 01:17:23,383
Hey! I'm... I'm Peter.

1063
01:17:23,667 --> 01:17:24,466
Tony.

1064
01:17:25,316 --> 01:17:26,860
What are you... What are you...
What are you doing here?

1065
01:17:26,925 --> 01:17:27,931
It's about time we met.

1066
01:17:28,158 --> 01:17:29,552
You've been getting my emails, right?

1067
01:17:30,083 --> 01:17:31,805
Yeah. Yeah.
Right?

1068
01:17:32,014 --> 01:17:33,015
Regarding the...

1069
01:17:33,017 --> 01:17:34,161
You didn't even tell me
