01:30:18,530 --> 01:30:19,969
or a squad of J-SOC guys,

1329
01:30:19,971 --> 01:30:22,073
with no compunction
about being impolite.

1330
01:30:24,702 --> 01:30:25,712
Come on.

1331
01:30:27,038 --> 01:30:27,997
<i>We found it.</i>

1332
01:30:29,874 --> 01:30:31,990
Their Quinjet's in hangar five,
north runway.

1333
01:30:36,172 --> 01:30:37,343
Alright, Lang.

1334
01:30:38,550 --> 01:30:39,736
Hey, guys, something,

1335
01:30:40,718 --> 01:30:41,862
What the hell was that?

1336
01:30:41,886 --> 01:30:43,788
I believe this is yours,
Captain America.

1337
01:30:44,055 --> 01:30:45,056
Oh, great.

1338
01:30:45,223 --> 01:30:46,534
Alright, there is two
on the parking deck.

1339
01:30:46,558 --> 01:30:48,119
One of them's Maximoff,
I'm gonna grab her.

1340
01:30:48,143 --> 01:30:49,635
Rhodey, you wanna take Cap?

1341
01:30:49,769 --> 01:30:51,771
Got two in the terminal,
Wilson and Barnes.

1342
01:30:51,938 --> 01:30:53,062
Barnes is mine.

1343
01:30:54,463 --> 01:30:55,779
Hey, Mr Stark, what should I do?

1344
01:30:55,802 --> 01:30:56,734
What we discussed.

1345
01:30:56,818 --> 01:30:57,878
Keep your distance, web them up.

1346
01:30:57,902 --> 01:30:59,112
Ok, copy that.

1347
01:31:03,992 --> 01:31:05,293
Move, Captain.

1348
01:31:05,743 --> 01:31:07,519
I won't ask a second time.

1349
01:31:09,937 --> 01:31:11,457
Look, I really don't want to hurt you.

1350
01:31:11,791 --> 01:31:13,209
I would not stress about it.

1351
01:31:25,430 --> 01:31:26,764
What the hell is that?

1352
01:31:26,931 --> 01:31:29,017
Everyone's got a gimmick now.

1353
01:31:35,730 --> 01:31:37,106
You have a metal arm?

1354
01:31:37,108 --> 01:31:38,454
That is awesome, dude.

1355
01:31:40,403 --> 01:31:42,069
You have the right to remain silent!

1356
01:31:56,597 --> 01:31:58,085
Sorry, Cap, this won't kill you,

1357
01:31:58,087 --> 01:31:59,407
but it ain't gonna tickle either.

1358
01:32:04,690 --> 01:32:06,608
Wanda, I think you hurt
Vision's feelings.

1359
01:32:06,610 --> 01:32:08,190
You locked me in my room.

1360
01:32:08,192 --> 01:32:09,847
Ok, first, that's an exaggeration.

1361
01:32:09,849 --> 01:32:11,759
Second, I did it to protect you.

1362
01:32:12,278 --> 01:32:13,597
Hey, Clint.
Hey, man.

1363
01:32:13,853 --> 01:32:15,718
Clearly, retirement doesn't suit you.

1364
01:32:15,730 --> 01:32:17,090
You got tired of shooting golf?

1365
01:32:17,254 --> 01:32:19,488
Well, I played 18, shot 18.

1366
01:32:20,690 --> 01:32:21,899
Just can't seem to miss.

1367
01:32:24,489 --> 01:32:25,782
First time for everything.

1368
01:32:25,949 --> 01:32:26,949
Made you look.

1369
01:32:37,502 --> 01:32:39,512
<i>Multiple contusions detected.</i>

1370
01:32:39,514 --> 01:32:41,041
Yeah, I detected that, too.

1371
01:32:48,888 --> 01:32:49,931
Oh, God!

1372
01:32:51,224 --> 01:32:52,850
Hey, buddy, I think you lost this!

1373
01:33:04,946 --> 01:33:06,239
Those wings carbon fibre?

1374
01:33:06,447 --> 01:33:07,612
Is this stuff coming out of you?

1375
01:33:07,639 --> 01:33:09,604
That would explain
the rigidity-flexibility ratio,

1376
01:33:09,606 --> 01:33:11,317
which, got to say,
that's awesome, man.

1377
01:33:11,319 --> 01:33:12,910
I don't know if you've
been in a fight before,

1378
01:33:12,912 --> 01:33:14,592
but there is usually
not this much talking.

1379
01:33:14,594 --> 01:33:15,757
Alright, sorry. My bad.

1380
01:33:20,795 --> 01:33:22,422
Guys, look, I'd love to keep this up,

1381
01:33:22,424 --> 01:33:24,051
but I've only got one job here today,

1382
01:33:24,053 --> 01:33:27,014
and I got to impress Mr Stark,
so, I'm really sorry.

1383
01:33:30,862 --> 01:33:32,442
You couldn't have done that earlier?

1384
01:33:33,433 --> 01:33:34,520
I hate you.

1385
01:33:41,346 --> 01:33:42,109
Great.

1386
01:33:42,306 --> 01:33:43,409
Hey, Cap, heads-up!

1387
01:33:45,486 --> 01:33:46,863
Throw it at this.

1388
01:33:47,447 --> 01:33:48,489
Now!

1389
01:33:51,993 --> 01:33:53,286
Oh, come on!

1390
01:33:56,247 --> 01:33:58,815
Oh man, I thought it was a water truck.

1391
01:33:59,951 --> 01:34:00,816
Sorry.

1392
01:34:03,087 --> 01:34:04,422
Alright, now I'm pissed.

1393
01:34:05,381 --> 01:34:06,716
Is this part of the plan?

1394
01:34:06,883 --> 01:34:08,426
Well, my plan was go easy on them.

1395
01:34:08,428 --> 01:34:09,513
You wanna switch it up?

1396
01:34:12,055 --> 01:34:13,055
There's our ride.

1397
01:34:15,516 --> 01:34:16,517
Come on!

1398
01:34:25,633 --> 01:34:26,717
Captain Rogers,

1399
01:34:27,612 --> 01:34:30,615
I know you believe
what you're doing is right.

1400
01:34:31,407 --> 01:34:33,081
But for the collective good,

1401
01:34:33,409 --> 01:34:35,272
you must surrender now.

1402
01:34:52,845 --> 01:34:54,246
What do we do, Cap?

1403
01:34:55,473 --> 01:34:56,536
We fight.

1404
01:34:58,518 --> 01:35:00,144
This is gonna end well.

1405
01:35:06,901 --> 01:35:08,319
They're not stopping.

1406
01:35:08,447 --> 01:35:09,447
Neither are we.

1407
01:35:40,476 --> 01:35:41,602
We're still friends, right?

1408
01:35:41,769 --> 01:35:43,364
Depends on how hard you hit me.

1409
01:35:52,276 --> 01:35:53,729
You were pulling your punches.

1410
01:35:58,494 --> 01:35:59,704
I didn't kill your father.

1411
01:35:59,836 --> 01:36:01,181
Then why did you run?

1412
01:36:19,765 --> 01:36:21,809
That thing does not obey
the laws of physics at all.

1413
01:36:21,811 --> 01:36:24,064
Look, kid, there is a lot going on here
that you don't understand.

1414
01:36:24,066 --> 01:36:25,351
Mr Stark said you'd say that.

1415
01:36:35,028 --> 01:36:37,072
He also said to go for your legs.

1416
01:36:48,920 --> 01:36:50,254
Clint, can you get him off me?

1417
01:36:50,421 --> 01:36:51,589
Buckled in?

1418
01:36:51,756 --> 01:36:53,331
Yeah. No, I'm good.

1419
01:36:53,341 --> 01:36:55,482
I'm good, Arrow Guy.
Let's go! Let's go!

1420
01:37:17,114 --> 01:37:18,491
Stark tell you anything else?

1421
01:37:18,658 --> 01:37:21,236
That you're wrong.
You think you're right.

1422
01:37:21,953 --> 01:37:23,329
That makes you dangerous.

1423
01:37:28,334 --> 01:37:29,752
Guess he had a point.

1424
01:37:34,840 --> 01:37:36,019
You got heart, kid.

1425
01:37:36,246 --> 01:37:37,194
Where you from?

1426
01:37:37,834 --> 01:37:38,844
Queens.

1427
01:37:40,471 --> 01:37:41,472
Brooklyn.

1428
01:37:47,436 --> 01:37:48,479
Friday?

1429
01:37:48,563 --> 01:37:50,314
<i>We have some weapon systems offline.</i>

1430
01:37:50,316 --> 01:37:51,056
What?

1431
01:37:51,190 --> 01:37:53,725
Oh, you're gonna have
to take this into the shop.

1432
01:37:53,934 --> 01:37:55,269
Who's speaking?

1433
01:37:55,436 --> 01:37:56,880
It's your conscience.

1434
01:37:57,105 --> 01:37:59,048
We don't talk a lot these days.

1435
01:37:59,156 --> 01:38:01,681
Friday?
<i>Deploying fire suppression system.</i>

1436
01:38:05,663 --> 01:38:06,664
Oh, boy!

1437
01:38:16,007 --> 01:38:17,031
We got to go.

1438
01:38:17,062 --> 01:38:18,580
That guy's probably in Siberia by now.

1439
01:38:18,582 --> 01:38:19,733
We got to draw out the flyers.

1440
01:38:20,081 --> 01:38:21,654
I'll take Vision, you get to the jet.

1441
01:38:21,656 --> 01:38:23,459
No, you get to the jet!

1442
01:38:23,598 --> 01:38:24,598
<i>Both of you!</i>

1443
01:38:27,018 --> 01:38:28,495
The rest of us aren't getting out of here.

1444
01:38:28,519 --> 01:38:29,663
As much as I hate to admit it,

1445
01:38:29,687 --> 01:38:31,147
<i>if we're gonna win this one,</i>

1446
01:38:31,149 --> 01:38:32,734
<i>some of us might have to lose it.</i>

1447
01:38:33,005 --> 01:38:34,710
<i>This isn't the real fight, Steve.</i>

1448
01:38:35,192 --> 01:38:36,805
Alright, Sam. What's the play?

1449
01:38:37,028 --> 01:38:39,113
We need a diversion. Something big.

1450
01:38:40,865 --> 01:38:42,491
I got something kinda big.

1451
01:38:42,575 --> 01:38:44,105
<i>But I can't hold it very long.</i>

1452
01:38:44,327 --> 01:38:46,450
<i>On my signal, run like hell.</i>

1453
01:38:46,537 --> 01:38:48,155
<i>And if I tear myself in half,</i>

1454
01:38:48,351 --> 01:38:50,550
<i>don't come back for me.</i>
He's gonna tear himself in half?

1455
01:38:50,603 --> 01:38:51,663
You sure about this, Scott?

1456
01:38:51,917 --> 01:38:52,974
<i>I do it all the time.</i>

1457
01:38:53,286 --> 01:38:54,083
<i>I mean, once.</i>

1458
01:38:54,598 --> 01:38:55,345
<i>In a lab.</i>

1459
01:38:55,546 --> 01:38:56,618
<i>Then I passed out.</i>

1460
01:38:57,381 --> 01:38:59,116
I'm the boss, I'm the boss, I'm the boss.

1461
01:39:15,274 --> 01:39:16,776
Holy shit!

1462
01:39:21,072 --> 01:39:23,236
Ok, tiny dude is big now.
He's big now.

1463
01:39:24,992 --> 01:39:26,077
I guess that's the signal.

1464
01:39:26,327 --> 01:39:27,787
Way to go, Tic Tac!

1465
01:39:29,664 --> 01:39:31,082
Give me back my Rhodey.

1466
01:39:34,752 --> 01:39:35,961
I got him.

1467
01:39:58,429 --> 01:40:01,153
Ok, anybody on our side
hiding any shocking

1468
01:40:01,155 --> 01:40:03,269
and fantastic abilities
they'd like to disclose,

1469
01:40:03,372 --> 01:40:04,685
I'm open to suggestions.

1470
01:40:12,373 --> 01:40:13,999
You wanna get to them,

1471
01:40:14,166 --> 01:40:15,681
you got to go through me.

1472
01:40:42,319 --> 01:40:43,779
We haven't met yet.

1473
01:40:46,365 --> 01:40:48,419
I'm Clint.
I don't care.

1474
01:41:15,895 --> 01:41:16,895
Get off!

1475
01:41:31,786 --> 01:41:33,496
Something just flew in me!

1476
01:41:57,728 --> 01:41:58,966
You're not gonna stop.

1477
01:41:59,458 --> 01:42:00,459
You know I can't.

1478
01:42:01,372 --> 01:42:02,498
I'm gonna regret this.

1479
01:42:06,153 --> 01:42:07,446
Go.

1480
01:42:13,118 --> 01:42:15,457
Hey, guys, you ever see
that really old movie,

1481
01:42:16,084 --> 01:42:17,412
Empire Strikes Back?

1482
01:42:17,414 --> 01:42:18,892
<i>Jesus, Tony, how old is this guy?</i>

1483
01:42:18,916 --> 01:42:20,060
I don't know, I didn't carbon-date him.

1484
01:42:20,084 --> 01:42:21,274
He's on the young side.

1485
01:42:23,128 --> 01:42:26,257
You know that part
where they're on the snow planet,

1486
01:42:27,508 --> 01:42:29,009
with the walking thingies?

1487
01:42:31,428 --> 01:42:32,614
Maybe the kid's onto something.

1488
01:42:32,638 --> 01:42:33,861
High now, Tony. Go high.

1489
01:42:42,106 --> 01:42:43,107
Yes!

1490
01:42:43,649 --> 01:42:45,234
That was awesome!

1491
01:42:59,957 --> 01:43:02,960
Does anyone have any orange slices?

1492
01:43:08,632 --> 01:43:09,726
Kid, you alright?
Hey!

1493
01:43:11,635 --> 01:43:13,242
Same side. Guess who.
Get out of me!

1494
01:43:13,270 --> 01:43:14,530
Hi. It's me.

1495
01:43:14,889 --> 01:43:16,029
Hey, man.
Yeah.

1496
01:43:16,114 --> 01:43:17,449
That was scary.
Yeah.

1497
01:43:17,516 --> 01:43:19,143
You're done, alright?

1498
01:43:19,483 --> 01:43:20,398
What?
You did a good job.

1499
01:43:20,400 --> 01:43:21,881
I'm good, I'm fine.
Stay down.

1500
01:43:21,883 --> 01:43:22,683
No, it's good. I got to get him back.

1501
01:43:22,685 --> 01:43:23,840
You're going home or I'll call Aunt May!

1502
01:43:23,981 --> 01:43:25,049
You're done!

1503
01:43:25,316 --> 01:43:26,145
Wait.

1504
01:43:26,525 --> 01:43:27,594
Mr Stark, wait.

1505
01:43:27,971 --> 01:43:29,300
I'm not done. I'm not,

1506
01:43:31,864 --> 01:43:33,707
Ok, I'm done. I'm done.

1507
01:43:50,174 --> 01:43:52,414
I said I'd help you find him,
not catch him.

1508
01:43:52,927 --> 01:43:54,511
There's a difference.

1509
01:44:01,054 --> 01:44:02,054
I'm sorry.

1510
01:44:02,937 --> 01:44:04,021
Me, too.

1511
01:44:04,939 --> 01:44:05,939
It's as I said.

1512
01:44:06,440 --> 01:44:07,818
Catastrophe.

1513
01:44:21,038 --> 01:44:22,873
Vision, I got a bandit on my six.

1514
01:44:27,628 --> 01:44:28,407
<i>Vision!</i>

1515
01:44:28,796 --> 01:44:31,088
<i>You copy? Target his thruster,
turn him into a glider.</i>

1516
01:44:45,980 --> 01:44:46,927
Rhodey!

1517
01:44:49,036 --> 01:44:50,587
Tony, I'm flying dead stick.

1518
01:44:58,909 --> 01:44:59,976
Rhodes!

1519
01:45:12,631 --> 01:45:13,791
Read vitals.

1520
01:45:14,258 --> 01:45:15,609
<i>Heartbeat detected.</i>

1521
01:45:15,917 --> 01:45:17,533
<i>Emergency medical is on its way.</i>

1522
01:45:22,928 --> 01:45:23,928
I'm sorry.

1523
01:45:41,874 --> 01:45:43,274
<i>Good morning, at your service.</i>

1524
01:45:43,298 --> 01:45:45,024
Good morning Mrs Leiber.

1525
01:45:45,654 --> 01:45:47,189
This is room 201.

1526
01:45:47,382 --> 01:45:48,483
<i>Hi Mr Müller.</i>

1527
01:45:48,586 --> 01:45:50,521
<i>Bacon and black coffee
again today?</i>

1528
01:45:51,608 --> 01:45:53,151
You know me so well.

1529
01:45:54,745 --> 01:45:56,653
Hello? Your breakfast is here.

1530
01:45:57,691 --> 01:45:59,012
May I let myself in?

1531
01:46:07,674 --> 01:46:08,874
Mr Müller?

1532
01:46:12,250 --> 01:46:13,450
Mr Müller?

1533
01:46:23,869 --> 01:46:25,496
What's gonna happen
to your friends?

1534
01:46:34,088 --> 01:46:35,317
Whatever it is,

1535
01:46:36,215 --> 01:46:37,441
I'll deal with it.

1536
01:46:40,830 --> 01:46:42,917
I don't know if I'm worth all this, Steve.

1537
01:46:50,229 --> 01:46:51,855
What you did all those years,

1538
01:46:52,898 --> 01:46:54,199
It wasn't you.

1539
01:46:55,234 --> 01:46:56,817
You didn't have a choice.

1540
01:46:58,195 --> 01:46:59,239
I know.

1541
01:47:02,399 --> 01:47:03,735
But I did it.

1542
01:47:18,841 --> 01:47:20,168
How did this happen?

1543
01:47:21,176 --> 01:47:22,723
I became distracted.

1544
01:47:25,472 --> 01:47:27,399
I didn't think that was possible.

1545
01:47:29,017 --> 01:47:30,586
Neither did I.

1546
01:47:47,244 --> 01:47:50,247
The doctors say
he shattered L4 through S1.

1547
01:47:50,414 --> 01:47:52,721
Extreme laceration to the spinal cord.

1548
01:47:53,333 --> 01:47:55,796
Probably looking at
some form of paralysis.

1549
01:47:59,298 --> 01:48:00,841
Steve's not gonna stop.

1550
01:48:01,714 --> 01:48:02,757
If you don't either,

1551
01:48:02,759 --> 01:48:04,154
Rhodey's gonna be
the best case scenario.

1552
01:48:04,178 --> 01:48:05,345
You let them go, Nat.

1553
01:48:05,512 --> 01:48:06,555
We played this wrong.

1554
01:48:06,558 --> 01:48:07,482
We?

1555
01:48:08,432 --> 01:48:11,118
Boy, it must be hard to shake
the whole double agent thing.

1556
01:48:11,120 --> 01:48:12,521
It sticks in the DNA.

1557
01:48:14,271 --> 01:48:17,159
Are you incapable of
letting go of your ego,

1558
01:48:17,169 --> 01:48:19,029
for one goddamn second?

1559
01:48:23,595 --> 01:48:25,525
T'Challa told Ross what you did, so...

1560
01:48:27,187 --> 01:48:28,560
they're coming for you.

1561
01:48:29,661 --> 01:48:31,914
I'm not the one that needs
to watch their back.

1562
01:48:41,048 --> 01:48:42,424
What am I looking at, Friday?

1563
01:48:42,507 --> 01:48:44,421
<i>Priority upload from Berlin police.</i>

1564
01:48:47,930 --> 01:48:49,431
Fire up the chopper.

1565
01:48:55,395 --> 01:48:57,275
<i>The Task Force called
for a psychiatrist</i>

1566
01:48:57,277 --> 01:48:59,032
<i>as soon as Barnes was captured.</i>

1567
01:48:59,191 --> 01:49:01,485
<i>The UN dispatched
Doctor Theo Broussard</i>

1568
01:49:01,487 --> 01:49:02,945
<i>from Geneva within the hour.</i>

1569
01:49:03,111 --> 01:49:04,864
<i>He was met by this man.</i>

1570
01:49:04,947 --> 01:49:06,462
Did you run facial recognition yet?

1571
01:49:06,464 --> 01:49:07,429
<i>What do I look like?</i>

1572
01:49:08,049 --> 01:49:09,329
I don't know.
I've been picturing a redhead.

1573
01:49:09,493 --> 01:49:11,036
<i>You must be thinking
of someone else.</i>

1574
01:49:11,246 --> 01:49:12,289
Must be.

1575
01:49:12,371 --> 01:49:15,140
<i>The fake doctor is actually
Colonel Helmut Zemo.</i>

1576
01:49:16,291 --> 01:49:17,960
<i>Sokovian Intelligence.</i>

1577
01:49:19,544 --> 01:49:21,505
<i>Zemo ran Echo Scorpion,</i>

1578
01:49:21,836 --> 01:49:24,102
<i>a Sokovian covert kill squad.</i>

1579
01:49:26,343 --> 01:49:27,844
So what happened
to the real Broussard?

1580
01:49:27,846 --> 01:49:29,855
<i>He was found dead
in a Berlin hotel room.</i>

1581
01:49:29,972 --> 01:49:33,048
<i>Where police also found
a wig and facial prosthesis,</i>

1582
01:49:33,049 --> 01:49:37,095
<i>approximating the appearance
of one James Buchanan Barnes.</i>

1583
01:49:37,938 --> 01:49:39,445
Son of a bitch.

1584
01:49:41,733 --> 01:49:43,601
Get this to Ross.
<i>Yes, boss.</i>

1585
01:51:17,329 --> 01:51:19,206
<i>This is Raft Prison Control.</i>

1586
01:51:19,331 --> 01:51:21,692
<i>You're cleared for landing, Mr Stark.</i>

1587
01:51:54,241 --> 01:51:56,201
So? You got the files?

1588
01:51:56,451 --> 01:51:57,619
Let's reroute the satellites,

1589
01:51:57,786 --> 01:51:59,704
start facial scanning for this Zemo guy.

1590
01:51:59,871 --> 01:52:01,541
You seriously think
I'm gonna listen to you

1591
01:52:01,543 --> 01:52:03,729
after that fiasco in Leipzig?

1592
01:52:04,376 --> 01:52:06,570
You're lucky you're not
in one of these cells.

1593
01:52:37,492 --> 01:52:39,820
The Futurist, gentlemen!

1594
01:52:40,287 --> 01:52:42,547
The Futurist is here!

1595
01:52:43,023 --> 01:52:44,524
He sees all!

1596
01:52:45,208 --> 01:52:48,295
He knows what's best for you,
whether you like it or not.

1597
01:52:48,879 --> 01:52:50,180
Give me a break, Barton.

1598
01:52:50,230 --> 01:52:52,291
<i>I had no idea they'd put you here.
Come on.</i>

1599
01:52:53,672 --> 01:52:55,886
Yeah, well, you knew
they'd put us somewhere, Tony.

1600
01:52:56,260 --> 01:52:59,253
Yeah, but not some
super-max floating ocean pokey.

1601
01:52:59,380 --> 01:53:01,757
You know this place is for maniacs.
This is a place for...

1602
01:53:02,031 --> 01:53:03,124
Criminals?

1603
01:53:04,436 --> 01:53:05,846
Criminals, Tony.

1604
01:53:06,730 --> 01:53:08,752
Think that's the word you're looking for.

1605
01:53:10,358 --> 01:53:11,401
Right?

1606
01:53:12,027 --> 01:53:13,625
That didn't used to mean me.

1607
01:53:14,279 --> 01:53:15,697
Or Sam, or Wanda.

1608
01:53:16,111 --> 01:53:17,173
But here we are.

1609
01:53:17,805 --> 01:53:18,982
Because you broke the law.

1610
01:53:19,082 --> 01:53:20,387
Yeah.
I didn't make you.

1611
01:53:21,703 --> 01:53:23,243
You read it, you broke it.

1612
01:53:25,081 --> 01:53:26,950
You're all grown up,
you got a wife and kids.

1613
01:53:27,375 --> 01:53:28,328
I don't understand,

1614
01:53:28,352 --> 01:53:30,305
why didn't you think about them
before you chose the wrong side?

1615
01:53:31,842 --> 01:53:33,803
You got to watch your back with this guy.

1616
01:53:35,050 --> 01:53:36,877
There's a chance he's gonna break it.

1617
01:53:38,678 --> 01:53:41,577
Hank Pym always said
you never can trust a Stark.

1618
01:53:42,724 --> 01:53:43,732
Who are you?

1619
01:53:44,893 --> 01:53:46,075
Come on, man.

1620
01:53:48,063 --> 01:53:49,105
How's Rhodes?

1621
01:53:49,201 --> 01:53:51,437
They're flying him
to Columbia Medical tomorrow so...

1622
01:53:52,255 --> 01:53:53,423
fingers crossed.

1623
01:53:55,222 --> 01:53:56,682
What do you need?
They feed you yet?

1624
01:53:58,698 --> 01:54:00,200
You're the good cop, now?

1625
01:54:00,909 --> 01:54:02,845
I'm just the guy who needs
to know where Steve went.

1626
01:54:02,969 --> 01:54:04,554
Well, you better go get a bad cop,

1627
01:54:04,621 --> 01:54:06,807
because you're gonna have
to go Mark Fuhrman on my ass,

1628
01:54:06,831 --> 01:54:08,248
to get information out of me.

1629
01:54:09,000 --> 01:54:10,940
Well, I just knocked
the A out of their AV.

1630
01:54:11,086 --> 01:54:13,964
We got about 30 seconds before
they realise it's not their equipment.

1631
01:54:14,923 --> 01:54:16,053
What'd you do?

1632
01:54:16,132 --> 01:54:17,345
Get it back up!

1633
01:54:18,760 --> 01:54:19,760
Just look.

1634
01:54:20,762 --> 01:54:21,994
Because that,

1635
01:54:22,495 --> 01:54:24,775
is the fellow who was
supposed to interrogate Barnes.

1636
01:54:26,059 --> 01:54:28,812
Clearly, I made a mistake.
Sam, I was wrong.

1637
01:54:28,854 --> 01:54:29,928
That's a first.

1638
01:54:30,381 --> 01:54:32,126
Cap is definitely off the reservation,

1639
01:54:32,128 --> 01:54:33,968
but he's about to need
all the help he can get.

1640
01:54:34,901 --> 01:54:36,442
We don't know each other very well.
You don't have to...

1641
01:54:36,444 --> 01:54:38,102
Hey, it's alright.

1642
01:54:46,541 --> 01:54:47,781
Look, I'll tell you,

1643
01:54:48,373 --> 01:54:49,821
but you have to go alone...

1644
01:54:50,143 --> 01:54:51,463
and as a friend.

1645
01:54:53,003 --> 01:54:54,045
Easy.

1646
01:54:57,085 --> 01:54:57,948
Stark?

1647
01:54:58,633 --> 01:55:00,284
Did he give you anything on Rogers?

1648
01:55:00,286 --> 01:55:01,499
Nope. Told me to go to hell.

1649
01:55:01,501 --> 01:55:03,252
I'm going back
to the compound instead but...

1650
01:55:03,597 --> 01:55:05,439
you can call me anytime.

1651
01:55:05,724 --> 01:55:07,904
I'll put you on hold.
I like to watch the line blink.

1652
01:56:16,920 --> 01:56:18,522
You remember that time
we had to ride back

1653
01:56:18,546 --> 01:56:20,757
from Rockaway Beach
in the back of that freezer truck?

1654
01:56:20,921 --> 01:56:23,069
Was that the time
we used our train money

1655
01:56:23,176 --> 01:56:24,481
to buy hot dogs?

1656
01:56:24,552 --> 01:56:27,800
You blew three bucks trying to win
that stuffed bear for a redhead.

1657
01:56:28,429 --> 01:56:29,430
What was her name, again?

1658
01:56:29,432 --> 01:56:31,606
Dolores. You called her Dot.

1659
01:56:31,810 --> 01:56:33,570
She's got to be
a hundred years old right now.

1660
01:56:33,723 --> 01:56:34,869
So are we, pal.

1661
01:56:44,489 --> 01:56:46,574
He can't have been here more
than a few hours.

1662
01:56:46,741 --> 01:56:48,543
Long enough to wake them up.

1663
01:57:30,910 --> 01:57:31,911
You ready?

1664
01:57:32,078 --> 01:57:33,079
Yeah.

1665
01:57:46,676 --> 01:57:48,678
You seem a little defensive.

1666
01:57:50,013 --> 01:57:51,339
It's been a long day.

1667
01:57:51,973 --> 01:57:53,974
At ease, Soldier.
I'm not currently after you.

1668
01:57:53,975 --> 01:57:55,185
Then why are you here?

1669
01:57:56,269 --> 01:57:58,238
Could be your story's not so crazy.

1670
01:57:59,105 --> 01:58:00,105
Maybe.

1671
01:58:01,733 --> 01:58:04,442
Ross has no idea I'm here.
I'd like to keep it that way.

1672
01:58:05,612 --> 01:58:07,265
Otherwise, I got to arrest myself.

1673
01:58:08,907 --> 01:58:10,587
Well, that sounds like
a lot of paperwork.

1674
01:58:14,245 --> 01:58:15,538
It's good to see you, Tony.

1675
01:58:15,747 --> 01:58:16,879
You too, Cap.

1676
01:58:17,874 --> 01:58:20,126
Hey, Manchurian Candidate,
you're killing me.

1677
01:58:20,210 --> 01:58:22,009
There's a truce here. You can drop,

1678
01:58:42,148 --> 01:58:43,483
I got heat signatures.

1679
01:58:43,650 --> 01:58:44,709
How many?

1680
01:58:46,852 --> 01:58:47,852
One.

1681
01:59:06,673 --> 01:59:08,467
<i>If it's any comfort,</i>

1682
01:59:09,050 --> 01:59:10,552
<i>they died in their sleep.</i>

1683
01:59:17,600 --> 01:59:20,087
<i>Did you really think
I wanted more of you?</i>

1684
01:59:21,855 --> 01:59:23,073
What the hell?

1685
01:59:24,357 --> 01:59:26,150
<i>I'm grateful to them, though.</i>

1686
01:59:27,352 --> 01:59:28,895
<i>They brought you here.</i>

1687
01:59:33,491 --> 01:59:34,952
<i>Please, Captain.</i>

1688
01:59:35,368 --> 01:59:37,282
<i>The Soviets built
this chamber to withstand</i>

1689
01:59:37,284 --> 01:59:39,870
<i>the launch blast of UR-100 rockets.</i>

1690
01:59:40,145 --> 01:59:41,791
I'm betting I could beat that.

1691
01:59:41,958 --> 01:59:43,758
<i>Oh, I'm sure you could, Mr Stark.</i>

1692
01:59:44,210 --> 01:59:45,465
<i>Given time.</i>

1693
01:59:46,212 --> 01:59:47,797
<i>But then you'd never
know why you came.</i>

1694
01:59:48,006 --> 01:59:50,466
You killed innocent people in Vienna
just to bring us here?

1695
01:59:57,265 --> 02:00:00,894
I've thought about
nothing else for over a year.

1696
02:00:01,561 --> 02:00:03,168
I studied you.

1697
02:00:03,813 --> 02:00:05,231
I followed you.

1698
02:00:06,177 --> 02:00:07,827
But now that you're standing here,

1699
02:00:08,003 --> 02:00:09,695
I just realised,

1700
02:00:11,988 --> 02:00:14,590
there is a bit of green
in the blue of your eyes.

1701
02:00:17,070 --> 02:00:18,953
How nice to find a flaw.

1702
02:00:20,055 --> 02:00:21,308
You're Sokovian.

1703
02:00:22,875 --> 02:00:24,208
Is that what this is about?

1704
02:00:24,375 --> 02:00:27,879
Sokovia was a failed state
long before you blew it to hell.

1705
02:00:27,980 --> 02:00:28,713
No.

1706
02:00:30,465 --> 02:00:32,805
I'm here because I made a promise.

1707
02:00:36,638 --> 02:00:37,847
You lost someone?

1708
02:00:41,726 --> 02:00:43,770
I lost everyone.

1709
02:00:45,605 --> 02:00:47,190
And so will you.

1710
02:00:53,859 --> 02:00:57,116
An empire toppled
by its enemies can rise again.

1711
02:00:58,201 --> 02:01:00,328
But one which crumbles from within?

1712
02:01:01,955 --> 02:01:03,456
That's dead.

1713
02:01:04,582 --> 02:01:05,583
Forever.

1714
02:01:14,347 --> 02:01:15,745
I know that road.

1715
02:01:18,429 --> 02:01:19,430
What is this?

1716
02:01:42,704 --> 02:01:44,330
<i>Help my wife.</i>

1717
02:01:45,456 --> 02:01:47,649
<i>Please. Help.</i>

1718
02:01:53,339 --> 02:01:54,587
<i>Sergeant Barnes?</i>

1719
02:01:56,175 --> 02:01:57,332
<i>Howard!</i>

1720
02:02:05,101 --> 02:02:06,144
<i>Howard!</i>

1721
02:02:43,352 --> 02:02:44,803
No, Tony. Tony.

1722
02:02:54,317 --> 02:02:55,526
Did you know?

1723
02:02:58,099 --> 02:02:59,350
I didn't know it was him.

1724
02:02:59,447 --> 02:03:01,966
Don't bullshit me, Rogers.
Did you know?

1725
02:03:06,111 --> 02:03:07,154
Yes.

1726
02:04:03,823 --> 02:04:04,938
Get out of here!

1727
02:04:16,479 --> 02:04:17,560
It wasn't him, Tony.

1728
02:04:17,567 --> 02:04:18,866
HYDRA had control of his mind!

1729
02:04:18,885 --> 02:04:19,693
Move!

1730
02:04:19,735 --> 02:04:20,736
It wasn't him!

1731
02:04:29,745 --> 02:04:31,080
<i>Left boot-jet failing.</i>

1732
02:04:31,956 --> 02:04:33,883
<i>Flight systems compromised.</i>

1733
02:04:34,792 --> 02:04:35,792
Crap.

1734
02:04:49,557 --> 02:04:51,274
He's not gonna stop. Go.

1735
02:05:14,290 --> 02:05:15,291
Come on, come on.

1736
02:05:15,458 --> 02:05:17,138
<i>Targeting system's knackered, boss.</i>

1737
02:05:17,210 --> 02:05:18,210
I'm eyeballing it.

1738
02:05:36,812 --> 02:05:38,439
Do you even remember them?

1739
02:05:38,829 --> 02:05:40,316
I remember all of them.

1740
02:06:03,172 --> 02:06:04,965
This isn't gonna change what happened.

1741
02:06:05,341 --> 02:06:06,348
I don't care.

1742
02:06:07,385 --> 02:06:08,653
He killed my mom.

1743
02:07:10,239 --> 02:07:12,876
<i>You should have seen his little face.
Just try, ok?</i>

1744
02:07:13,743 --> 02:07:15,010
<i>I'm going to bed.</i>

1745
02:07:15,745 --> 02:07:16,862
<i>I love you.</i>

1746
02:07:25,379 --> 02:07:27,416
I almost killed the wrong man.

1747
02:07:28,924 --> 02:07:30,521
Hardly an innocent one.

1748
02:07:31,093 --> 02:07:32,620
This is all you wanted?

1749
02:07:33,763 --> 02:07:35,847
To see them rip each other apart.

1750
02:07:40,227 --> 02:07:42,414
My father lived outside the city.

1751
02:07:43,968 --> 02:07:45,713
I thought we would be safe there.

1752
02:07:46,734 --> 02:07:48,192
My son was excited.

1753
02:07:48,778 --> 02:07:51,185
He could see the Iron Man
from the car window.

1754
02:07:52,615 --> 02:07:55,078
I told my wife, don't worry.

1755
02:07:55,993 --> 02:07:57,394
They're fighting in the city.

1756
02:07:57,998 --> 02:07:59,518
We're miles from harm.

1757
02:08:02,291 --> 02:08:04,027
When the dust cleared,

1758
02:08:05,359 --> 02:08:07,071
and the screaming stopped,

1759
02:08:08,589 --> 02:08:12,402
it took me two days
until I found their bodies.

1760
02:08:14,845 --> 02:08:16,230
My father,

1761
02:08:17,264 --> 02:08:20,667
still holding my wife
and son in his arms.

1762
02:08:25,201 --> 02:08:26,603
And the Avengers?

1763
02:08:28,275 --> 02:08:29,406
They went home.

1764
02:08:31,987 --> 02:08:33,737
I knew I couldn't kill them.

1765
02:08:34,323 --> 02:08:36,666
More powerful men
than me have tried.

1766
02:08:37,736 --> 02:08:38,611
But...

1767
02:08:39,161 --> 02:08:41,413
if I could get them to kill each other,

1768
02:08:45,835 --> 02:08:47,955
I'm sorry about your father.

1769
02:08:49,046 --> 02:08:50,681
He seemed a good man.

1770
02:08:52,675 --> 02:08:54,176
With a dutiful son.

1771
02:08:58,889 --> 02:09:01,016
Vengeance has consumed you.

1772
02:09:03,367 --> 02:09:05,003
It's consuming them.

1773
02:09:09,733 --> 02:09:11,819
I am done letting it consume me.

1774
02:09:15,531 --> 02:09:17,867
Justice will come soon enough.

1775
02:09:21,203 --> 02:09:23,038
Tell that to the dead.

1776
02:09:27,543 --> 02:09:29,654
The living are not done with you, yet.

1777
02:09:33,090 --> 02:09:34,951
<i>You can't beat him hand-to-hand.</i>

1778
02:09:36,677 --> 02:09:37,845
Analyze his fight pattern.

1779
02:09:38,137 --> 02:09:39,305
<i>Scanning.</i>

1780
02:09:44,018 --> 02:09:45,238
<i>Countermeasures ready.</i>

1781
02:09:47,229 --> 02:09:48,357
Let's kick his ass.

1782
02:10:01,911 --> 02:10:03,204
He's my friend.

1783
02:10:03,954 --> 02:10:04,997
So was I.

1784
02:10:12,046 --> 02:10:14,131
Stay down. Final warning.

1785
02:10:28,604 --> 02:10:29,974
I could do this all day.

1786
02:11:37,131 --> 02:11:38,800
That shield doesn't belong to you.

1787
02:11:41,010 --> 02:11:42,323
You don't deserve it.

1788
02:11:42,845 --> 02:11:44,453
My father made that shield!

1789
02:12:20,549 --> 02:12:22,384
Meals at 8 and 5.

1790
02:12:22,551 --> 02:12:24,178
Toilet privileges twice a day.

1791
02:12:26,555 --> 02:12:28,724
Raise your voice, zap.

1792
02:12:29,391 --> 02:12:31,393
Touch the glass, zap.

1793
02:12:31,727 --> 02:12:33,729
You step out of line, you deal with me.

1794
02:12:33,896 --> 02:12:35,865
Please, step out of line.

1795
02:12:38,275 --> 02:12:39,693
So how does it feel?

1796
02:12:40,611 --> 02:12:42,657
To spend all that time, all that effort,

1797
02:12:44,016 --> 02:12:44,658
and...

1798
02:12:45,949 --> 02:12:47,383
to see it fail,

1799
02:12:48,249 --> 02:12:49,895
so spectacularly.

1800
02:12:54,083 --> 02:12:55,234
Did it?

1801
02:13:21,617 --> 02:13:23,210
It's just the first pass.
Yeah.

1802
02:13:23,212 --> 02:13:25,421
Give me some feedback,
anything you think of.

1803
02:13:25,422 --> 02:13:27,891
Shock absorption, lateral movement.

1804
02:13:28,617 --> 02:13:29,618
Cup holder?

1805
02:13:29,637 --> 02:13:31,357
You may wanna think about
some AC down in,

1806
02:13:35,249 --> 02:13:36,489
Let's go. I'll give you a hand.

1807
02:13:36,625 --> 02:13:38,293
No. No. Don't help. Don't help me.

1808
02:13:54,351 --> 02:13:55,644
138.

1809
02:13:56,478 --> 02:13:58,235
138 combat missions.

1810
02:13:59,209 --> 02:14:00,913
That's how many I've flown, Tony.

1811
02:14:01,275 --> 02:14:03,838
Every one of them
could've been my last, but I flew them.

1812
02:14:06,391 --> 02:14:07,953
Because the fight needed to be fought.

1813
02:14:08,388 --> 02:14:10,015
It's the same with these Accords.

1814
02:14:10,534 --> 02:14:13,643
I signed because it was
the right thing to do.

1815
02:14:15,998 --> 02:14:17,841
And yeah, this sucks. This is...

1816
02:14:19,334 --> 02:14:20,747
This is a bad beat.

1817
02:14:23,213 --> 02:14:24,840
But it hasn't changed my mind.

1818
02:14:26,508 --> 02:14:27,556
I don't think.

1819
02:14:38,312 --> 02:14:39,688
You ok?
Oh, yeah.

1820
02:14:43,025 --> 02:14:45,373
Are you Tony Stank?

1821
02:14:46,236 --> 02:14:48,677
Yes, this is, this is Tony Stank.

1822
02:14:49,125 --> 02:14:50,415
You're in the right place.

1823
02:14:50,563 --> 02:14:51,973
Thank you for that!

1824
02:14:52,534 --> 02:14:54,369
Never dropping that, by the way.

1825
02:14:54,536 --> 02:14:56,455
Table for one, Mr Stank.

1826
02:14:56,607 --> 02:14:58,207
Please, by the bathroom.

1827
02:15:04,410 --> 02:15:05,410
<font color="#ff8000"><i>Tony,</i></font>

1828
02:15:06,423 --> 02:15:07,976
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I'm glad you're back at the compound.</i></font>

1829
02:15:08,550 --> 02:15:11,239
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I don't like the idea of you
rattling around a mansion by yourself.</i></font>

1830
02:15:11,762 --> 02:15:13,138
<font color="#ff8000"><i>We all need family.</i></font>

1831
02:15:14,556 --> 02:15:16,147
<font color="#ff8000"><i>The Avengers are yours.</i></font>

1832
02:15:16,410 --> 02:15:18,043
<font color="#ff8000"><i>Maybe more so than mine.</i></font>

1833
02:15:19,186 --> 02:15:21,518
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I've been on my own since I was 18.</i></font>

1834
02:15:22,523 --> 02:15:25,192
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I never really fit in anywhere,</i></font>

1835
02:15:25,353 --> 02:15:26,457
<font color="#ff8000"><i>even in the Army.</i></font>

1836
02:15:28,737 --> 02:15:31,793
<font color="#ff8000"><i>My faith's in people, I guess.</i></font>

1837
02:15:32,074 --> 02:15:33,283
<font color="#ff8000"><i>Individuals.</i></font>

1838
02:15:34,087 --> 02:15:36,731
<font color="#ff8000"><i>And I'm happy to say that,
for the most part,</i></font>

1839
02:15:37,454 --> 02:15:38,805
<font color="#ff8000"><i>they haven't let me down.</i></font>

1840
02:15:41,083 --> 02:15:43,410
<font color="#ff8000"><i>Which is why I can't let them down either.</i></font>

1841
02:15:47,548 --> 02:15:50,585
<font color="#ff8000"><i>Locks can be replaced,
but maybe they should not.</i></font>

1842
02:15:52,803 --> 02:15:54,423
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I know I hurt you, Tony.</i></font>

1843
02:15:55,097 --> 02:15:56,091
<font color="#ff8000">I guess I thought

1844
02:15:56,515 --> 02:15:58,265
<font color="#ff8000"><i>by not telling you about your parents,</i></font>

1845
02:15:58,267 --> 02:15:59,775
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I was sparing you, but...</i></font>

1846
02:16:00,769 --> 02:16:03,128
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I can see now that
I was really sparing myself.</i></font>

1847
02:16:03,939 --> 02:16:05,138
<font color="#ff8000"><i>And I'm sorry.</i></font>

1848
02:16:06,108 --> 02:16:07,896
<font color="#ff8000"><i>Hopefully one day you can understand.</i></font>

1849
02:16:09,152 --> 02:16:10,904
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I wish we agreed on the Accords.</i></font>

1850
02:16:10,988 --> 02:16:12,028
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I really do.</i></font>

1851
02:16:12,739 --> 02:16:14,300
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I know you're doing what you believe in,</i></font>

1852
02:16:14,324 --> 02:16:15,746
<font color="#ff8000"><i>and that's all any of us can do.</i></font>

1853
02:16:15,951 --> 02:16:17,189
<font color="#ff8000"><i>That's all any of us should.</i></font>

1854
02:16:17,411 --> 02:16:19,296
<i>Priority call from Secretary Ross.</i>

1855
02:16:19,496 --> 02:16:21,255
<i>There's been a breach at the Raft prison.</i>

1856
02:16:22,978 --> 02:16:24,204
Yeah, put him through.

1857
02:16:26,223 --> 02:16:27,480
<i>Tony, we have a problem.</i>

1858
02:16:27,699 --> 02:16:29,701
Please hold.
<i>No, don't.</i>

1859
02:16:32,259 --> 02:16:33,556
<font color="#ff8000"><i>So no matter what,</i></font>

1860
02:16:34,803 --> 02:16:35,866
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I promise you,</i></font>

1861
02:16:36,263 --> 02:16:37,373
<font color="#ff8000"><i>if you need us,</i></font>

1862
02:16:38,689 --> 02:16:39,949
<font color="#ff8000"><i>if you need me,</i></font>

1863
02:16:45,022 --> 02:16:46,315
<font color="#ff8000"><i>I'll be there.</i></font>

